{"sections":[{"backgroundImage":"ic_unified_ds.png","image":"ic_unified_ds.png","title":"Swift Package integration","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS iOS is exposed through an open source Swift Package hosted on GitHub, and provides several librairies for your needs.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"These librairies help to split products and make users able to select only what they need.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"SwiftUI is the only official supported framework.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"estimatedTimeInMinutes":10,"kind":"hero","xcodeRequirement":"Xcode 26","chapter":"Import of the Swift Package and choose its librairies"},{"kind":"tasks","tasks":[{"title":"Import the Swift Package and the libraries","contentSection":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS for iOS is an open source Swift Package available on GitHub under MIT license.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The package and the librairies must be added through Xcode.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"contentAndMedia","mediaPosition":"trailing"}],"stepsSection":[{"media":"tutorial-1-ouds-swift-package.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Using Xcode, in your ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"project package dependencies"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":", add a new ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"dependency","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Search with the GitHub repository URL (https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios), and select the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"ouds-ios","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" dependency.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"You can then choose the ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"dependency rule"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" you want.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"To know which version you need, you can have a look on the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/wiki\/01-%E2%80%90-Available-API","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and also the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/Orange-OpenSource\/ouds-ios\/releases","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"caption":[],"type":"step","code":null,"runtimePreview":null},{"type":"step","code":null,"media":"tutorial-1-ouds-libraries.png","caption":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Add for example only the umbrella product merging all products mentioned above: ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSSwiftUI","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"runtimePreview":null,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once you downloaded the package, you will see several librairies are available."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"They can be embeded inside your "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"target"}]},{"type":"text","text":" librairies."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Things are separated to let users integrate only what they need and embed the abre minimum of content."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesContract"}]},{"type":"text","text":" library provides the main elements like the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":". The theme contract is defined inside it."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesOrange"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesSosh","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Sosh products, and contains also assets and all tokens for this theme."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSThemesWireframe"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Wireframe theme, which is a theme dedicated to mockups and prototypes."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDSThemesOrangeBusinessTools","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" provides the theme implementation for the Orange products but with constraints of sizes and spaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSComponents"}]},{"type":"text","text":" contains the SwiftUI OUDS components defined with the Figma specifications, and also useful view modifers."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensRaw"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensSemantic"}]},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSTokensComponents"}]},{"type":"text","text":" are librairies defining and providing the tokens for low level (raw),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"middle level (semantic) or component levels (high level)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSModules"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is for modules or rich components with extra logic."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDSFoundations"}]},{"type":"text","text":" is dedicated to some utilities and shared logic."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"anchor":"Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries"}]},{"kind":"assessments","assessments":[{"type":"multiple-choice","choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"I can contribute to OUDS using pull request","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS is open source, under MIT license, and hosted on GitHub. Of course you can contribute!"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS supports officialy all Apple OS like visionOS, tvOS, watchOS, iPadOS, iOS and also CarPlay."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The main supported targets are iOS \/ iPadOS. However we do our best to support macOS and visionOS. tvOS, watchOS and CarPlay are not scoped yet.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"justification":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"OUDS supports officialy only SwiftUI. UIKit is very experimental and not recommended.","type":"text"}]}],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"OUDS provides UIKit components"}]}],"isCorrect":false}],"content":[],"title":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Which of these choices is correct?"}]}]},{"title":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Which imports of the OUDS Swift Package products can I choose?","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"multiple-choice","content":[],"choices":[{"isCorrect":true,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can import all products provided by the Swift Package, and tailor your choice to keep only the ones needed."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Even if we recommend to choose only the atomic products you need, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" product wraps all of them."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some of the available products depending to my needs, or only "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSSwiftUI"},{"type":"text","text":" if I am very lazy and don’t care about my app size."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"isCorrect":false,"justification":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need to chose the products the Swift package provides"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"None, only the Swift package dependency matter","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}],"anchor":"Check-Your-Understanding"},{"action":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-2-instanciate-theme","type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Get started","overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}]},"title":"Instanciate and inject a theme","kind":"callToAction","abstract":[{"text":"The theme is exposed as one object which will be injected inside your SwiftUI view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The theme provides all tokens which defines in the end the rendering of everything.","type":"text"}],"featuredEyebrow":"Tutorial"}],"kind":"project","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/tutorials\/oudsthemescontract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies"]}],"metadata":{"role":"project","title":"Swift Package integration","categoryPathComponent":"Table-Of-Contents","category":"Orange Unified Design System"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents","modules":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/Table-Of-Contents\/Import-of-the-Swift-Package-and-choose-its-librairies","projects":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies","sections":[{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Import-the-Swift-Package-and-the-libraries","kind":"task"},{"reference":"doc:\/\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorials\/OUDSThemesContract\/tutorial-1-package-and-librairies#Check-Your-Understanding","kind":"